<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mouse1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mouse,</orth> subst. the animal Mus: <bibl n="shak. luc 555" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 555</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.223" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 223</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.223" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 223</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.172" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.6.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 6, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 40</bibl> (cf. <emph>Dun</emph>). <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.104" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 10</bibl> <cit><quote>(not a m. stirring).</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 89</bibl></cit>. Per. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.0." default="NO" valid="yes">III Prol. 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 78</bibl>. Used as a term of endearment: <cit><quote>what's your dark meaning, m.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 19</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>good my m. of virtue, answer me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 69</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>call you his m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 183</bibl></cit>.<lb />Plur. <cit><quote>mice:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 64</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.18" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 18</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>